FBIS4-36161 "drnes109_j_94014" FBIS-NES-94-109 Daily Report 6 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen League Envoy Denies Sanaa Shelled Aden Oil Refinery League Envoy Denies Sanaa Shelled Aden Oil Refinery NC0606164794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1545 GMT 6 May 94 NC0606164794 Cairo MENA Arabic BFN [Text] Cairo, 6 Jun (MENA) -- Ahmad Muhammad Luqman, permanent representative of the Republic of Yemen to the Arab League, has denied news agency reports that warplanes bombed storage tanks in the Aden oil refinery in south Yemen. In a statement made today, the Yemeni ambassador said such an attack is not part of Sanaa's military strategy. He explained that since the outbreak of war, Sanaa has been eager to keep all vital and civilian installations in the southern governorates away from military operations.
